<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Fambamtil</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-04 01:13:11</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Here is the stuff on Dex and Agi...<BR>
... agility dosn't dirrectly decrease the chance of being hit, if you have ever tryed on a mith bp you know what it does, mith bp is only 17ac right? well slap it on and there you have it! an extra 30ac!!! So, it increases your ac which in turn decreases chances of getting hit, and to my beliefe, decreases how hard you are hit, although I am probably wrong.  And as how for Dex was made out to be, it is way better than that: Dex increases your procs of course, forgot the other common stuff, but most impportantly it increases your chances of hitting in the first place.  Dexterity is accuracy. Their you have it (O:<BR>
Just my 2cp<BR>
<BR>
Fambamtil<BR>
Gnome Rogue of the 9'th blade sharpening ^crusaders of war^</font></td></tr></table>
