<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Cronilaus</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-26 09:32:40</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Dex does the following: raises the chance of a proc, increase the ability to hit harder with fist/weapon,raises the ability to increase in the skills based around offense.<BR>
<BR>
Agi does the following: raises the chance of dodging an attack, raises the chance of parry/riposte,raises the ability to increase in the skills based around defense.<BR>
<BR>
We tested this with 8 different classes, and was proven beyond a doubt. An increase of just 5 in dex made a pgt proc up to 15% more against a low blue pincer beetle. And hits of up to 25% more where experienced.<BR>
<BR>
An increase of 5 agi.. on the other hand, had no effect on the procing, but the subjects where hit for less, and hit less often. Data was tabulated over 15 fights with beetles..5 with agi add 5 with dex adds...with the original 5 being to determine a starting hit/defense/proc base.<BR>
<BR>
Note the caster classes we used used a water crys staff  not a pgt, obviously, and the results where around the same.. though most had to be healed, as no spells where cast.<BR>
<BR>
End of arguement</font></td></tr></table>
